headline: Moody’s Puts France on Watch for a Credit Downgrade. Why It’s Become a ‘Hot Mess.’
summary: France has its issues, and credit-rating firm  Moody’s  is finally acknowledging them.  Moody’s changed its outlook on French government bonds to Negative from Stable.  The firm rates France’s bonds Aa3, the equivalent of AA-, and a downgrade would bring them to A1.
